Company Description

Mirantis is the fastest way to modern apps, providing containers-as-a-service at enterprise scale. The company uses a unique as-a-service model to deliver Kubernetes and related open source software, empowering developers to build, share and run their applications anywhere - from public cloud to hybrid cloud to the edge. Mirantis serves many of the world’s leading enterprises, including Adobe, DocuSign, Liberty Mutual, PayPal, Reliance Jio, Splunk, STC, Vodafone, and Volkswagen. Learn more at www.mirantis.com.

Job Description

For more than 13 years, Agilent Development Center at Mirantis has been working as part of Agilent on building laboratory solutions to meet the full spectrum of customers' needs. Our team is growing, and today we are looking for talented QA Engineers who would join our department.

As a QA Engineer in our center at Mirantis, you will be part of a team that designs and develops new scientific software components. We build solutions for... organizing laboratories in distributed environments, storing experimental measurements, managing instruments, security and access control, data management with flexible, scalable on-prem & cloud storage options, and API allowing partner integrations.

Your primary responsibilities will include close work with the team and Product Owner on project requirements, design of testing strategies, automated and manual testing for desktop, server, and web applications.

Qualifications
• 2+ years of experience in Software Testing and Quality Assurance;
• Good knowledge of software development life cycle, Agile methodologies, testing methodologies, and testing tools;
• Proactive self-starter with a keen eye for details, with a focus on end-user experiences, and the ability to go above and beyond to ensure a high-quality release;
• Experience developing detailed test cases, filing detailed defect reports, and providing relevant data for test reporting;
• Troubleshoot and provide detailed debug information for expediting issue resolution;
• Experience developing automated tests and frameworks (C#, Java, etc.) will be an advantage;
• Experience with CI for automated testing (Jenkins, pipe-lines) will be an advantage;
• Good in written and spoken English.

Opportunities we can offer:
• Active participation in the development of strategies for manual and automated testing for crucial components of Agilent’s products;
• Influence on such aspects of projects life as requirements definition and planning, testing workflows, functionality and appearance of each project;
• Professional development in QA automation and CI;
• Close work with Agilent employees from the US, Europe, and Australia in a collaborative development environment.

Additional Information

We offer:

- Work in a leading company in cloud computing industry

- High-energy atmosphere of open source projects

- Multiple opportunities for on-the-job learning and professional growth

- Flexible schedule (both full-time and part time)

- Participation in OpenStack and Kubernetes cloud design projects

- Supervision by experienced mentors

- On-site English courses

- Opportunity to make a difference in the world of cloud computing

Mirantis ranked in the top 50 of G2's Best IT Cloud Products of 2021!
